anna play SZ you prolly want a class that can solo. And I wouldn't play a melee on RZ unless you have a group of friends you're going to lvl up with..<br>
<br>
Problem with monks is you can't really get any decent resist gear till BD stuff. The weight limit doesn't allow us to wear alot of the stuff lower lvl melees can wear, so they get rooted alot..<br>
<br>
Monks do very well against casters in enclosed areas, even at lower levels. And they're great in group pvp. They lack kill shot skills like backstab, HT, or nuke so it's pretty easy for people to just zone or gate from them if they try to gank. Monk is a good class if you plan to group pk. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udimitrakosx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dimitrakosx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/12/02 8:23:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=671.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Monks</span><hr size=1> monks have low innate resistances, especially MR.  They also have low HP's which makes them hard to stand up to caster or melee.  They need a few expensive pieces like WS coat/ Tranix crown + the regular BD gear to really be a force.  With epic, Tstaff, and other high dammage weapons.  Picture a Tstaff proc, break out stronger weapon, and pop inner flame thats alot of dammage.<br>
<br>
As a caster, monk epic haste will really make a differnece when it comes to interrupts.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udynamitestick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DynamiteStick</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/12/02 3:45:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=671.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Don't even think about playing a monk unless you can joust well. I mean, very well. You have @#%$ for HPs, @#%$ for resists, no mana, and no ranged ability. Unless you can land a lot more hits than your opponent is expecting, you won't be very effective.<br>
-spinfusor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulethdarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lethdarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/12/02 8:48:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=671.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Monks arent really that well at solo pvp til high end, but they're deadly at training if you play on sz. Nothing quite as fun as training 3 ntov wyverns onto 40 people into HoT and watching them drop like dominoes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujphive.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JPhive</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.tripod.co.uk/redhotant/icons/iconoc16.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/16/02 1:13:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=671.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> get a tstaff and go fight a wiz and pray that u proc while the caster is sitting down...then u get in a lot of hits no problem...but yes jousting is key when fighting other melee's...a good rogue will still mess u up nicely if they know what they are doing cuz they can still BS u while jousting <p><img src="http://www.intentor.org/eq/number1.jpg">
